Items.Value: The Railgun's rounds give a short stun effect.
The shield emitters are upgraded to output energy faster, increasing the recharge rate by 50%.
Capable of firing a suite of space-to-ground indirect fire that can quickly free an entire battlefield from oppression.
A grenade launcher that shoots incendiary grenades.
Pushing the boundaries of bionic engineering, this armor collects and dispenses a number of vital fluids, several of which are soon to be declassified.
Disintegrating expanding projectile with massive damage, poor ballistics and accuracy. Causes chock in enemies hit by the round.
The standard prism for laser rifles.
Additional mounts for bombs allows for one more strike before the Eagle has to return and rearm.
Armor explodes <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c> after the wearer dies.
A welcome sight in all Democratic neighborhoods, this armor inspires both civil pride and civic obedience.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The 'LIBERATOR' is the well known standard service rifle for the SEAF. A balance of power, firerate, and weight has made it into a reliable and trusty companion for every soldier.

Produced by Galactic Arms and Equipment (GAE), this service rifle has survived the test of time and catapulted GAE into success and renown.
A flashlight mounted to the weapon to illuminate your target while aiming.

Based on the uniform of Jackle 6, a veteran of the Viper Commandos who held off an entire Terminid brood on Nublaria in the First Galactic War with nothing but a machine gun, pocket knife, and Orbital Laser Strikes.
An advanced, mostly self-operating prospecting drill fitted into a Hellpod. Handles soil sample extraction, analysis and data upload with minimal necessary input from an operator.
A domestic version of this armor is available for citizens who wish to perform efficient home renovation projects.
A lightly-armored reconnaissance vehicle mounted with a heavy machinegun.
A longer revolver barrel that results in a higher muzzle velocity and lower recoil at the cost of worse handling.
A powerful dual magazine pump-action shotgun, with limited armor penetration. Ideal for small and fast targets.
A plasma igniter that reduces the vertical recoil created when firing.
A high-caliber submachine gun which can be fired with one hand. Has a relatively low rate of fire.
An automated turret with an extremely high rate of fire. Caution: does not check if friendly units are in line of fire.
Improved ammunition storage allows for the turret to be more liberal with ammunition, adding an additional round to each salvo.
Helps prevent Helldivers from flinching when hit.
A heavy-duty submachine gun that fires large-caliber rounds, with a slower rate of fire to manage the high recoil. Ideal for use at close to medium range.
The reload time has been improved, lowering the cooldown between uses by 15 seconds.
A high-damage revolver, which can be reloaded with single rounds. A heavy-hitting and reliable sidearm.
A stationary ballistic cover with a mounted grenade launcher. Can protect multiple Helldivers from small arms fire.
This cape depicts the inner workings of a medical device submitted to the Ministry of Science 70 years ago, and is bound to clear their patent approval process any day now.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The Napalm airstrike drops a row of bombs containing an extremely flammable liquid with a fairly long burn time, effectively creating a wall of fire. Great for stopping the enemy in their tracks as a universal rule for all life in the galaxy seems to be to avoid fire. The fire doesn't burn hot enough to do any significant damage to heavily armored targets.
This high-visibility armor allows it's bearer to be easily seen through smoke, fog, and spewing viscera.
A common magazine type in the Super Earth military, favoring sustained fire over handling.
This suit's plutonium-238 nuclear battery enables environmental scanning long after the user has ceased operation.
Disintegrating expanding projectile with massive damage, poor ballistics and accuracy. Causes chock in enemies hit by the round.
THE CAPE OF STARS AND SUFFRAGE

For backline-focused Helldivers. 
Specializes in providing suppressive fire and fire support.
First deployed in the mines of Cyberstan, where it offered protection against explosions in the hydrogen-rich caverns.
Explosive tipped projectile that does high damage against massive unarmored targets.
An improved formula for napalm fuel is used, resulting in a significantly longer burn time on the ground.
Further reduces recoil when crouching or prone by <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c>.
A blend of ammunition replacing almost every other round with an armor-piercing bullet. Greatly improves efficiency against all but the lightest targets.
Provides <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c> damage resistance to fire, allowing bearer to rest assured in their inflammability.

The HVAPT-rounds are designed for maximizing penetration capabilities at the cost of some destructive potential. Excellent at destroying weak points in lighter vehicles but requires pinpoint accuracy.
Reloading of the Orbital Cannon is improved, allowing for less time between uses. Cooldown reduced by 10 seconds.
A turret which fires electrical charges at targets in close range. To avoid friendly fire, remain prone.
A high-caliber sniper rifle effective over long distances against light vehicle armor. This rifle must be aimed downscope.
Offering camouflage in snowy environments, surplus sets of this armor are used by nature photographers and keen hunters alike.
Promotional armor made by SUMY Corp. as part of a highly successful marketing campaign for frozen yogurt.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] Super Earth issued a contract for creation of a new main armament for the Super Destroyers of the HELLDIVERS. The contract was won by MORGUNSON who developed the LIBERTY CANNON able to deliver precise shots from relatively long distances delivering various kinds of ammunition.
Armor Piercing Tipped Ammunition that does less damage to unarmored targets.
The Vehicle can be called in one more time during missions.
Hyper Velocity Round with a serious kick.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A rack of SRID-12 aspect seeking missiles used to take out flying targets. The Missiles have extremely intelligent guidance and good flight characteristics in most atmospheres. The Eagle pilot will target a variety of flying targets and make sure to clean up the skies for you. Great if you are overwhelmed with a large number of enemy fliers.
The suit was once designed to hold a variety of battlefield medical equipment. Now it holds a generous supply of stims.

NOT YET IMPLEMENTED The 'KNIGHT' is a submachine gun with an extreme rate of fire and an advanced recoil-dampening system. Capable of putting its entire magazine on target within seconds, this weapon is best used on close to medium range.

The bullets quickly lose speed and as such decrease impact force on longer distances. In the SEAF this weapon is mostly issued to vehicle and flight crews as well as supporting personnel.
A heavier, rugged scope for use on less precise support weapons.
The end result of several billion Super Credits and 12 years of reseach into creating "the Soldier of Tomorrow."
An automated assembly line where all Hellpod armaments are constructed by precise, non-sentient robotic arms.
Embodies the ethos of Manifest Democracy—that it is our voter-given responsibility to emancipate the savage, un-Liberated galaxy. To rest only when every planet is safe, civilized, and Free.
On impact the projectile melts the armor of the target.
The number of times the Rocket Sentry can be called down during a missions is increased from 3 to 4 times.
A grenade packed with high explosive.

NOT IMPLEMENTED The 'SENATOR' is a heavy revolver using the long 12mm pistol cartridge capable of putting down large enemies in a single or a few shots.

The major downside of the revolver is the low magazine count and heavy recoil, but many consider them to be completely offset by the heavy impact of the long 12mm cartridge.
A modified Punisher shotgun firing exploding plasma rounds. Fire carefully - exploding plasma can injure squadmates.
Wearers of this cape know that even enemies of Freedom deserve to be equal. Equally dead.
You can choose between Flak and APHET rounds in the weapon function.
The Energy Shield can take 50% more damage before the shield breaks and needs to recharge again.
A humane grenade launcher firing high-powered arc grenades.
A high-precision burst-fire plasma rifle that must be charged to fire.
With genuine gold accents, 74% of colonists voted this armor the set they would most like to be buried in.
Self-propelled rocket with high damage and good armor piercing capability
A vastly improved afterburner is installed giving the EAGLE a faster pull out time and shortening the time before it is ready to attack again.
Expanding projectile that does massive damage against unarmored targets.
A barrage of napalm bombs, creating a wall of fire which will stop the enemy in their tracks.
The ammunition in the drone-carried gun is replaced with explosive ammunition, improving its damage.
Increases the amount of additional canisters you can carry.
Expanding projectile that does massive damage against unarmored targets.
A high explosive grenade which detonates on first impact.
A submachine gun with a helical-feed magazine, which gives the weapon a higher ammo capacity while making it more front-heavy. Produced by Stål Arms.
Space optimizations allows for an additional magazine to be carried, increasing the number of times the turret can fire.
Space is made for more ammunition, allowing for longer firing times.
A vertical foregrip with an integrated tactical light.
Plasma cored warhead that detonates with super heated gas.
Lethal toxins are stored within the projectile which shatter on impact
The machinegun is equipped with a significantly larger magazine, holding 200 rounds.
Crew training for the gun crews allows for faster turnaround times between the uses of the cannons. Lowered cooldown by 15 seconds.
Crafted to deliver Justice to the darkest crevices of the galaxy.

For utility-focused Helldivers. 
Specializes in anti-tank weaponry and entrenchment warfare.
This cape's cropped length symbolizes the brevity of galactic conflicts, thanks to the efficiency of the Helldivers.
Fires concussive rounds that stagger enemies. Slower rate of fire than other SMGs.
The two stripes serve as a reminder of the two pillars of successful military campaigns: attack, and further attack.
Awarded to those promoted to their point of greatest competency, and beyond.
Disintegrating expanding projectile with massive damage, poor ballistics and accuracy. Causes chock in enemies hit by the round.
An automated cannon turret firing anti-tank ammunition over long ranges. Sacrifices agility for range and power.
A laser weapon firing a continuous beam. Doesn't require ammunition, but will need heat sink replaced if it overheats.
While early prototypes used shock-absorbing gels, this armor stabilizes aim with the use of internal gyroscopes.
At the edge of the Federation, sometimes Democracy has only one representative.
Explosive tipped projectile that does high damage against massive unarmored targets.
The loading mechanism is improved, allowing for shorter preparation time between each weapon call-in.
Round with high armor piercing capability due to the inner core forged out of Super Uranium.
This armor's nostalgic color scheme brings to mind beloved trappings of colonial yesteryear: concrete frontier domiciles, slate-colored civilian jumpsuits, and Space Settlers' Pie.
Armor Piercing Tipped Ammunition that does less damage to unarmored targets.
Improved gunpowder propels the projectile at higher velocity reducing the travel time and increasing damage.
A plasma igniter that creates a more volatile plasma bolt. The bolt has a larger explosion and more damage but has a shorter lifetime before exploding.
All Hail the Helldivers, whose devotion to Managed Democracy has never faltered.
One of the most durable engineer armors available, each set is quality tested by an impact with a full-grown Charger.
An incendiary grenade which ignites any targets and terrain within the blast radius. Use with caution.
An extra Supply Backpack is made ready at the start of the mission, allowing both to be deployed at once.

An assault rifle with a high-capacity drum magazine, good for providing sustained fire. 
Produced by Stål Arms.
Assigns a random voice to your Helldiver when you die.

An SMG that fires caseless ammunition and is equipped with a non-removable suppressor. 
Produced by Martian Armory.
Our heroic fallen live on in this cape, guiding its bearer's aim to the heart of those who killed them.
A modified Breaker shotgun offering improved armor penetration and accuracy, with exceptionally high levels of recoil.
The lightning can now split 1 more time between targets so it will increase the amount of possible targets from 2 to 3.
A lightweight flamethrower. Shoots pressurized fuel through a dispersion nozzle into an open flame. Safe.
A cape that strikes a subroutine emulating fear into the CPUs of all Automatons who conduct visual scans of it.
Atomizes caustic chemicals into a fine mist that liquifies sensitive electronics and tissues. Blinds and slows most enemies.
The Combat Walker is equipped with a larger fuel tank.
A fully-automatic shotgun with a high rate of fire, excellent for controlling crowds. Requires frequent reloading.
Extensive training with the dropping of this type of bomb allows the pilot to shave off some time when dropping it, making the bomb arrive faster.
High-velocity armor-piercing rounds, effective against medium vehicle armor.
Artists and sculptors have made countless attempts at depicting the face of Liberty, but the truth is that any citizen can see it—they need only requisition a mirror.
A scope with 10x magnification, good for long range on high accuracy weapons.
The default internal part for rifles. Gives no modifications to weapons.
This cape honors the Eagle pilots who would follow a Stratagem beacon into the very jaws of tyranny, even when the beacon's placement seems inscrutable to the non-Helldiver mind.

NOT IMPLEMENTED A fully automatic 20mm cannon fed from a hopper containing up to two clips of 5 shots each at a time. Extremely flexible battlefield role due to the amount of variable ammunition available. The standard round is an Armor Piercing High Explosive Tracer great against heavy infantry and light vehicles. But other ammunition offers everything from anti-air capabilities to anti-tank.
Incendiary capsules that contain E-710 and a primer, sets targets on fire.
Assembled from pieces of recovered Helldiver armor and SEAF gear, for those who won't let a lack of full body protection keep them from the battlefront.
Explosive tipped projectile that does high damage against massive unarmored targets.
Deploys mines that release gas on activation, temporarily blinding and slowing most enemies.
A compact, low caliber machine gun. Trades power for ease of use, with faster reloading than heavier machine guns.
Good for medium to long range and the maximum magnification normally used for general weapons.
Painted by visionary artist Silas Garm during an intense fever, this symbol represents Humanity's great Galactic endeavor: the blood-soaked dawn of Lasting Peace.
Deploys a defensive incendiary minefield, which will set both terrain and targets alight when triggered.
The Helldiver Skull is said to strike fear in the hearts of foes attempting to sneak up on those wearing this cape.
A faithful replica of the armor worn at The Battle of Liberty Peak. Honor their legacy, and wear it with pride.
Order the Eagle Fighter to return to the ship, where it can restock its armaments.
Compact and flexible, this kevlar armor adds minimal mass, making it a common choice for Helldiver fitness tests.
A choir of patriotic schoolchildren sings the Super Earth anthem to each cape as the final step in its production.
A fully-automatic cannon effective against light vehicle armor. Includes support backpack required for reloading.
The Railgun can overcharge for one second more. This makes it safer to use or give even more damage if you dare.
A plasma pistol that charges each shot until the trigger is released. Plasma projectiles explode on impact.
An expendable missile launcher equipped with four laser-guided missiles.
A laser pistol that fires a continuous beam. Does not require ammo but can overheat and need to change batteries.
The clasps on this cape are made from melted down Automaton housings—evidence of Democracy's inevitable triumph.
The Orbital Gas Round has been improved with more lethal gas that kills faster.
An upgrade to the missile racks extends the amount of missiles that are carried, allowing for more runs before having to rearm.
Detonates on impact, covering the immediate vicinity in self-igniting white phosphorus.
The backpack is loaded with more rounds from 4 to 5 rounds.
A large bomb obliterating almost any target close to impact. Make sure to clear the area.
A precision artillery salvo over a small area, perfect for taking out concentrated enemy units.
When the Illuminate threatened Super Earth, the very Heart of Democracy, the Helldivers answered the call.
A high-pressure nozzle is installed which allows the flames to reach further before losing their forward momentum. Extends the range from 18 to 25 meters.
Pulling the trigger halfway fires single fire and all the way automatic fire. Only works while in Full-Auto mode.
A turret firing static field generators that slow the advance of enemies.
The backpack is loaded with 1 more Missile
Improved loading mechanisms allow for shorter preparation time between each weapon call-in.

For frontline-focused Helldivers.
Specialized in utilizing disruption and resilience for close-range warfare.
The Backpack can have its teleport function triggered manually.
A "compliance weapon" to modify enemy behavior. The projectile temporarily stuns all targets within the strike radius.
The fire rate of the autocannons is increased from 200 to 300 rounds per minute.
This high-caliber marksman rifle trades magazine capacity and rate of fire for powerful, accurate shots.
A compact handgun-style flamethrower, able to project a jet of fire over short distances.
Firing jet-propelled rounds, the Dominator trades fire rate and magazine capacity for increased damage per projectile.
The Orbital Gas Round has been improved with longer-lasting gas clouds.
For optimal performance, the manufacturer recommends avoiding immersing this armor in salt water for prolonged periods.
Few pellets for lightly armored targets.
The eternal colors of Super Earth can never be tainted. Only quenched, by the blood of its enemies.
Although bulkier, it provides the effects of both a laser sight and a flashlight.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The 'PUNISHER' is a dual magazine pump operated 10g shotgun. The standard buckshot has a large spread but each pellet carries significantly more energy than a regular 12g shotgun. The spread can be offset by using various chokes, and due to the pump action and dual magazine, this shotgun is extremely suited for specialized ammunition.

Not used in the SEAF except for special operations, this shotgun is made available to the Helldivers straight from the manufacturer Browfors Arms.
A single-use target-seeking anti-aircraft missile launcher. Must be locked to target before firing.
Charges up to fire a powerful, explosive energy burst. Has a long cooldown period after firing.
A mark of stalwart loyalty bestowed only to those who have proved themselves worthy through unquestioning dedication.
An angled foregrip with an integrated laser sight.
An extra Supply Backpack is made available in case you lose your first one.
This classic armor set is recognized by every citizen: worn by the heroic Helldivers who battled and forever defeated the Terminids, Cyborgs, and Illuminate in the First Galactic War.
Because this prototype's wires operate at 400,000 volts, it also includes a handy rubber underlayer for insulation.
Single sabot that does massive damage and has high armor piercing capability.
A shorter revolver barrel that results in a lower muzzle velocity and higher recoil but improves handling.
A mighty rifle with a signature lever-action enabling single round reload. Powerful precision suited to mid- and long-range combat.
A tribute to the Liberation of Choepessa IV in the First Galactic War, in which so much orbital ordnance was detonated that its sun was occluded by ash for an entire lunar cycle.
Enables melee attacks to <c=#COLOR>remove larger obstacles</c>, such as fences.
A paint job for use in desert environments.
The Shield can be active for a longer time. Increased from 3 to 4 minutes.
While wearing the Jump Pack it will try to break a fall from a dangerously high height. This air-braking uses very little fuel and won't affect remaining jumps.
Forged for those watchful protectors who silently guide all Helldivers, asking no recognition whatsoever, besides a simple custom-made suit of armor only they get to wear.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The DMB-500 is a evolution on the classic bombs of human history. The approach of not having any guidance system in the bomb has allowed for packing it with unprecedented amounts of conventional explosives, making for a very large explosion and resulting crater. While the bomb is not specifically designed to take out armored targets, the explosion is massive enough that a close hit will kill almost anything, armored or not. The drawback is that the Eagle pilot has to take more care when delivering the payload to make sure that the target is hit, this increases the response time of the bomb in comparison to other Eagle payloads.
The magazine has a larger size.
A paint job that dares to stand out.
A powerful manned gun emplacement, capable of taking out armored targets at long ranges.
Provides <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c> resistance to fire, gas, acid, and electrical damage.
A stationary ballistic cover with a mounted light machine gun. Can protect multiple Helldivers from small arms fire.
The magazines are loaded with a 12.5mm anti material round every third round. This makes it more effective overall and also against more armored units.
"Prowl like a jaguar, strike like a viper." -Motto of the storied SEAF special operations unit whose real exploits were portrayed in the classic comic book series "Tales of the Viper Commandos."
In mountainous colonies, domestic variants of this armor are used to throw weather monitoring equipment uphill.
An advanced explosives compression technique allows the bomb to be packed with more explosives, resulting in a bigger boom.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The F-89 EAGLE is a jet fighter capable of carrying large amounts of ordnance as well as both atmospheric and limited spaceflight. The F-89 comes equipped with a 23mm cannon that can be used for strafing runs against ground targets. 
Once the Eagle is assigned to follow you into combat you can choose additional payloads for it to carry. The EAGLE is capable of delivering its ordnance with very low time intervals, but has limited carrying capacity and needs to be sent back to be rearmed should it run out. 
The eagle is also susceptible to enemy anti-air weaponry and caution is advised when calling in strikes near enemy AA.
An agile automated machine gun turret. Will fire at targets even if Helldivers will be caught in the crossfire.

NOT IMPLEMENTED A fully automatic grenade launcher capable of extreme Anti-Personnel destruction. The grenades have an arming time to prevent explosions that might occur close to the user, this will cause the grenades to ricochet so use caution when firing at close range.
A speed-loaded volley gun with three different firing modes and three different RPM options. Warning: recoil varies significantly between firing modes.
A barrage of high explosive rounds, fired from the Destroyer's high speed rotary autocannons.
A prism which creates a wider beam that has better armor piercing at wider angles at the cost of armor piercing at the best angle.
The SEAF standard pistol - offering a high fire rate, generous capacity, and fast reloading.
Domestic versions of this armor enable colonial farmers to plant crops and mines side by side, safely.
The cooldown between Tesla Tower shots is decreased from 3 to 2 seconds.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A continuation of the early A|GL-8 grenade launcher turret, this model packs a hefty punch and has variable fire distance. The turret fires in a high arch raining shots down from above, negating cover and other things in the way. The turret normally requires line of sight to its target to do the firing but this can be removed with some clever engineering.
An autonomous drone equipped with a laser rifle, providing 360° cover. Returns to backpack to cool down.
The ammunition feed is improved allowing shorter cooldowns between uses. Cooldown decreased by 15 seconds.
"We fear not poison, fear not death; spite our foes with every breath." From the beloved classic Hazard Pay: The Musical.
The Jump Pack can be used more often. The recharge cooldown is shorter.
Lethal toxins are stored within the projectile which shatter on impact
The Destroyer's laser cannon will sweep over the designated area, vaporizing all targets within the effective radius.
The Ballistic Shield is larger and will cover a larger part how the Helldiver.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A precision artillery barrage fired from the 84mm Atlas Gatling cannon of a Helldiver Destroyer in low orbit. Handy for when you have to level smaller areas of the battlefield or take out enemy concentrations. The shells themselves are capable of destroying armored targets, but requires a direct hit to do any significant amount of damage making it unreliable as an anti-tank option.
A humane compliance weapon with two separate magazines: one for armor-penetrating flechette rounds and one for stun rounds.
A heavily-armored walking exosuit equipped with a rocket launcher and a heavy machine gun.
The Orbital Lasers can target a larger area. Search area have been increased from 50 to 60m.

A top-loaded shotgun prominently featured in the final episode of "Obedient Democracy Support Troopers."
Produced by Martian Armory.
A semi-automatic ceremonial rifle equipped with a bayonet. Can be set to fire in three-shot bursts, to easily conduct the Fallen Hero's Salute.
Packed full of high performance gunpowder this round packs a serious punch as well as kick.

The A/AC-41 is a 40mm automatic cannon firing explosive anti-tank ammunition. The Turret is effective over long ranges and against armored targets, but has limitations when it comes to the turn speed as the servos required for the heavier than normal weight of the gun are slower. It is therefore recommended to place the turret a respectable distance from the enemy and in a position that has good fields of fire.
A cluster fragmentation grenade. The shrapnel submunition allows it to inflict damage over a large area.
A high-caliber rifle with high damage and penetration.
Packed full of high performance gunpowder this round packs a serious punch as well as kick.
Improvements to the ready ammunition storage allows the ORBITAL BARRAGE to fire an additional salvo before having new ammunition brought up.
Even among the most depraved of dissidents, the mere sight of this armor is enough to inspire a change of heart.
A quality product, this armor can destroy over 300,000 kilometers of fencing with no decline in operational efficiency.
The recharge delay is 2 sec shorter both after taking damage and after the energy is depleted.
The main ingredient in Super Earth liberation.
An accurate, armor-penetrating rifle, the BR-14 Adjudicator delivers righteous judgement to medium-sized enemies, though its restrictive magazine limits its effectiveness against large groups.
Commemorating the New Stockholm treaty on prisoners of war, this cape celebrates the right of all enemy combatants to a swift and merciful execution.
A drone that defends its user by firing caustic gas at nearby enemies, blinding and slowing them temporarily. Returns to backpack to refill.
Bearers of this armor ride no equine mount, but are nonetheless borne to battle atop the trusty steed of Liberty.
Has less resistance and requires less pressure before the weapon starts firing.
Packed full of high performance gunpowder this round packs a serious punch as well as kick.
A modified Liberator fitted with a scope and firing armor-piercing rounds, to help users take down armored targets.
With removal of the crewspace and improved automation, gives room for more ammunition, allowing for two additional salvos before rearming.
A projectile which explodes while airborne, creating a deadly rain of shrapnel. Not effective against heavy armor.
A machine gun designed for stationary use. Trades higher power for increased recoil and reduced accuracy.
Each servo-assisted limb contains 138 miniature motors, to support a natural gait and long-term spinal health.
A larger rocket pod allows for more rockets to be fired each run, increasing the chance that the target will be taken out.
A flare that illuminates the battlefield.
A replacement for a fallen comrade.
A targeted air strike unable to destroy buildings, but efficient at clearing smaller targets.
The Ballistic Shield can now manually detonate a flash charge on the front, stunning any enemies nearby.
Provides one-time, short-lived resuscitation upon death, given that the Helldiver's body is still intact.
A laser rifle, firing in short bursts. Does not need reloading, but if it overheats a new heat sink must be fitted.
Creates a <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c> chance of surviving a lethal hit.
A paint job for use in arctic environments.
A submachine gun with an extremely high rate of fire, which can be operated with one hand. Ideal for multitasking.
The breathing apparatus built into this equipment helps both soldiers and colonists thrive, even when assigned to planets with atmospheres rated "suboptimal," "extreme," and "character building."

The dauntless pioneers of the Great Expansion, facing the un-Democratic unknown, adopted the Way of the Bandolier. With the gusto of their covering fire making up for their modest accuracy, they strived to be perfectly aligned in their shared values, and ready to serve when called upon by the machine gun of civic duty.
Additional rocket pods are installed to allow for  one more attack run before the Eagle has to rearm.
Command Center of the Super Destroyer. The helm from which Helldivers deliver Freedom's mercy.
Electrostatically charged container that emits a distorting punch when it hits its target
The backpack needs less time to recharge between displacements. Cooldown is decreased from 60 to 45 seconds
The crew has been trained to fire two salvoes with 6 seconds fire time each. Retargeting between salvoes.
Shaving some material off the bomb casing allows for more explosive filler, resulting in a bigger boom.
A plasma igniter that reduces the vertical recoil and some of the horizontal recoil created when firing.
Triggers a stun explosion after the player has teleported. This gives the player time to recover from potential enemies.
A LAS-16 Sickle model with all overheating protections conveniently removed, allowing for far longer bursts of fire. Does more damage when overheated, at the cost of slightly burning the user.

A Dark Fluid-powered backpack that generates a portable micro-wormhole. This safe and well-understood technology allows the wearer to warp short distances. Warning: do not use while pack is overloaded.
The Rail Cannon can search a larger area to find an optimal target. Search radius is increased from 30m to 45m.
A representation of the thankfulness of those infinite descendants whose liberated existence we strive to ensure.
An angled vertical foregrip to improve the maneuverability of the weapon.

NOT IMPLEMENTED A high caliber sniper rifle capable of killing most infantry and other light targets with a single well placed shot. Even capable of disabling lighter vehicles by shooting out the engine, tires, or tracks.
In field tests, 84% of users said that the armor improved their posture and self-esteem.
A heavy one-handed blade. Slower to swing than other melee weapons, but deals more damage.
A symbol of Super Earth's Astral Promise: that every star shall one day illuminate throngs of joyous voters.

The 'JUSTICE' is a assault rifle that was created to aid Helldivers in battle when they need a higher caliber rifle. The magazine carries fewer rounds than the `LIBERATOR` assault rifle but each round is of a higher caliber, effective against medium armored targets.

Based upon the previous standard issue service rifle, this version is modified with a longer barrel and improved sight attachment options. Produced by Radow Weapons Technology, the rifle still finds use as a marksman rifle used in SEAF squads.
An expanded internal ammunition bay is installed making it possible for the EAGLE to engage with its cannons two more times before running out.
A plasma container with a 50% larger capacity.
Commonly replicated in stage adaptions of "Lady Liberty's Tower", in which young Diver Beatrick dons this armor to slay Oppressio, the Tyrant Rex.
The heavy machine gun can now switch between three different fire rates to conserve ammo or increase the damage output.
Although Super Citizen Miranda's true identity has been lost to time, most legal historians agree that she was once a patron of highly-efficient interrogation techniques.

NOT IMPLEMENTED The 'PEACEMAKER' is the standard issue sidearm for officers and security personnel. A small caliber pistol, what it lacks in stopping power, it makes up for in reliability.

Many consider their sidearm a trusted friend handy for emergency situations. Originally produced by MEY as a pistol for their internal security, the model had so many strengths that is was submitted for trials as the SEAFS standard issue sidearm and passed with flying colors.
This armor was designed by PFC Rodney A. Carmichael, the first Helldiver to use a stim on an ally instead of himself.
Fires powerful exploding bolts which do maximum damage upon direct impact. Gravity must be accounted for when aiming.
Improved gunpowder propels the projectile at higher velocity reducing the travel time and increasing damage.
The backpack is upgraded to hold more magazines for the drone, increasing the capacity from 4 to 8.

NOT IMPLEMENTED The 'SCYTHE' is a rifle based on experimental Super Earth developed laser technology. It fires a continuous beam capable of heating up surfaces to extreme temperatures in seconds.

The beam is focused on extreme distance but can be focused further using different prisms, allowing for greater damage if used correctly. Refocusing the beam reduces the efficiency for the non focused interval.

When donning the One True Flag, one must face the direction of Super Earth, recite the Super Earth Anthem, and salute one's own image in the nearest reflective surface. Wrongful discarding of this cape is a capital offense.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The A/RL-66 ROCKET TURRET is a valuable tool for the Helldivers as it provides autonomous anti tank capability. The Turret fires salvos of rockets and tries to asses the damage before firing again to save ammunition. Take care not to stand behind the turret due to the exhaust produced when it fires.
A paint job for use in forest environments.
The Atlas Automatic Cannon's ammunition storage has been improved. It now fires one more salvo.
The unblinking eye represents ceaseless vigilance against bugs and benevolent surveillance of all Helldivers.
Expands the storage capacity for excess heat to increase the fire duration. This increases the fire duration from 25 to 35 seconds.
The lightning can now split 3 more times between targets so it will increase the amount of possible targets from 3 to 6.
After extensive testing in Patriotic Rehabilitation Centers, this design was proved most terrifying to dissent-afflicted individuals.
The LAV can take more damage before it is destroyed.

A single solid lead projectile made to expand when it hits its target. Great for longer ranges and delivers a massive impact on whatever it hits. It's a soft projectile that has trouble with anything harder than medium armor, but it can still do damage to some heavier targets.
Creates a large, thick smoke screen to block targets' line of sight.
Designed by fashion legend RH Gant, the pattern seen on this cape also appears on domestic dresses and gun-warmers.
Armor-piercing explosive rounds, effective against light vehicle armor.
The symbol on this cape represents the pillars of freedom: duty, obedience, and loyalty.
This modest cape has been worn by those guarding the Chamber of Unanimous Decision since time immemorial.
Durable, waterproof, and thermally-lined, surplus units of this cape are favored by domestic campers, to make tents.
Stuns enemies performing melee attacks. Must recharge for <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c>.
A powerful automated turret, effective against armored targets. The turret will primarily aim at larger enemies.
Developed by the Ministry of Science while investigating the phenomenon known as The Gloom, this armor is non-permeable and squeak resistant.
The number of times the Autocannon Sentry can be called down during a missions is increased from 3 to 4 times.
The Missile needs 1 second less to lock onto the target.
Lethal toxins are stored within the projectile which shatter on impact
Features a utility belt with pockets that can be filled with any number of things, such as pocket knives, mementos from home, and interesting rocks.

For precision-focused Helldivers. 
Specializes in Eagle air support, mobility and long-range warfare.
A backpack which can be wielded as a one-handed ballistic shield, protecting against small arms fire.
This patriotic armor comes recommended by the Ministry of Expansion, empowering the wearer to re-seize from our enemies any territory that any human has laid claim to, at any point in time.
The three stripes on the pauldrons stand for the three principles of Super Earth: Liberty, Democracy, and Prosperity.
It is well-documented that soldiers raised on harsh planets have an advantage when fighting in similar environments; this insight is foundational to the Democratic Youth Scouts Exchange Program.

This cape recalls the popular folk tale of the "Freedomslingers": re-educated dissidents, seeking redemption on the Federation's Borderline, hunting dangerous thought-traitors in exchange for ballot bounties.
Featuring an ancient sun symbol and a distressed look, this cape reminds us that the light of Liberty is everlasting, and will keep shining even when we ourselves have become tattered and frayed.
The Mine deployer can now be deployed faster from the Destroyer. Spawn time reduced from 5 to 3 seconds.
The memory of the Martian training grounds will endure, even after all the Helldivers who trained there have passed, some day in the far future.
Named for Helldiver Jack Boote, who shut down 908 illegal broadcasts before retiring with honors.

As documented in the bestselling graphic novel "The Breach," the final mission of the 361st "Freedom's Flame" saw the storied unit deploy straight into the heart of a Supervolcano, sacrificing themselves to trigger an eruption and wipe out a massive Terminid swarm.
A modified Breaker shotgun firing incendiary projectiles. Generates heat during use, so limited to burst fire.
A modified Liberator firing concussive rounds which do less damage but stagger enemies.
The Crew has prepacked crates based on your team's loadout, further hastening the resupply of ammunition. Cooldown is reduced by 60 Seconds.

The AIRBURST STRIKE is a single larger specialized projectile fired from the Helldiver Destroyer's 408mm cannons. The shot is programmed to explode above the ground and separate into multiple flechettes, each with their own explosive warhead. Extremely effective against unarmored infantry, the fact that it's a single round allows for fairly frequent firing.
A magazine with a very high capacity at the cost of being bulky and heavy.
A single-use weapon that fires a missile containing napalm cluster bombs that release upon impact.
The Sniper Rifle is equipped with light weight magazines, making it possible to carry more during a mission.
This is essentially like firing small hand grenades at a target.
Rifle round with added micro-propellant that increases ballistics at the cost of velocity.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] A rack of semi-guided 100-kg bombs, intended to be dropped on a area target in a high speed flyby. The bomb pattern produces a carpet of explosions killing most infantry, but has a harder time affecting armored targets unless they are directly hit by one of the bombs. A great option for creating pause in an enemy advance or taking out larger concentrations of infantry.
The number of times the Gatling Sentry can be called down during a missions is increased from 3 to 4 times.
The Railgun's rounds have an improved lightweight casing that allows the Helldiver to carry more during a mission.
Upgrades to the target acquisition allows for more rounds on target. Each salvo fires two shots.
Users are advised not to scratch at the lacquer, as the Red 20,000 pigment that gives this armor its signature sheen may be correlated with rapid DNA unspooling.
An advanced angled foregrip to improve weapon stability.
A shorter magazine with lower capacity, making it lighter and easier to handle.
The number of times the Heavy Machine gun emplacement can be called in is increased from 3 to 4 times.

(NOT IMPLEMENTED) The JAR rifle fires a very heavy round with a small jet-propulsion charge at the end of it, accelerating the shot and extending its range greatly.

The weapon is very accurate but the large rounds are complicated and can not be fired too rapidly due to disturbing other projectiles with their backwash. Great at killing large tough things like alien crustaceans.
Inside the collar is embroidered: "Wherever I may plant my shield, know that I will never yield," and "machine washable."
An illumination flare is fired from your ship in orbit to light up the battlefield. It will start burning and give roughly 100 seconds of magnesium fueled light. Highly recommended on night missions.
A Hellpod containing a Super Solid State Drive, the peak of secure data storage. Used by Helldivers for everything from transfer of patriotic data to the sabotage of enemy mainframes.
The muted colors and relaxed, high-mobility fit make this a favorite among long-distance snipers and hide-and-seek champions alike.

The standard shotgun ammunition type. Fires a swarm of lead balls that spread over distance. Great for close combat and extremely effective against lightly armored targets. The spread can be modified by a choke (muzzle attachment) to be tighter or spread differently over longer distances. Virtually useless against armor.
This armor uses repurposed metal from verified sources, such as vending machine packaging and Automaton scrap, making it a sustainable choice for the environmentally conscious Helldiver.
The LAV can carry more magazines for the LMG mounts.
An automated flamethrower turret. Warning: fuel canister prone to explosion when ruptured.
Made famous by the "Truth Enforcers: Enforcers of Truth" mystery novels, this armor calls to mind those paragons of patriotism who protect us from treasonous lies.
Markers placed on the map will generate radar scans every <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c>.
Heavy Projectile with better damage and ballistics, the downside is the worse accuracy.
A very powerful but difficult-to-wield machine gun with intense recoil.
A single-use weapon specialized for damaging vehicle armor. Discarded after every use.
Supplies are always on standby and are immediately dispatched from the ship when called in.
The cape's shredded hem presages the unrelenting savagery its wielder will visit upon the nemeses of Freedom.
The number of times the Mortar Sentry can be called down during a missions is increased from 3 to 4 times.
A variation on the reflex sight.
The crest on this armor's shoulder shows friendlies that safety is near, and foes that they have reached the end of the road.
A projectile which releases a cloud of caustic gas, blinding and slowing most enemies.
A camo paint job for use in desert environments.
The CW-22 Kodiak armor was thoroughly pressure-tested by patriotic volunteers, as part of the "Test Subjects for Super-Earth" Citizen Advancement Program.
You can choose between HE and HEAT settings with the weapon function.
Each Hellpod is loaded with 4 weapons instead of 2.
The pattern used for this armor is the result of the Winter Camouflage Improvement Effort, which considered 136 entrants before determining the color white would best blend in with snow.
The HE rounds have a larger explosion radius and the HEAT rounds have a flatter armor piercing value so it will bounce less often.
With its rustic charm and huntsmanlike detailing, this armor evokes those heroic expansionists who braved the alien wilds and ushered in our current age of bio-uniformity.
By reminding Chemical Agents of proper distancing rules, this extraordinary innovation in cape design ensures that they never cause another unfortunate outbreak of Carcino-Plague.
The signature orange pauldron allows easy battlefield detection of the bearer, alive or dead, on ash-strewn battlefields.
The Arc Throwers arc will do more damage.
A reliable assault rifle with an antique iron sight, firing incendiary ammunition.
"The ground is just another obstacle that hasn't yet been cleared." - SGM Janet Jones, Excavation Corps Founder.
The patented fabric absorbs visible, infrared, and ultraviolet radiation, to prevent detection by all known species.

For technology-focused Helldivers. 
Specialized in utilizing offensive and defensive high-tech gadgetry in warfare.
The Sniper Rifle is equipped with larger magazines that can carry more rounds.
This armor, together with its friendly-faced helmet, is instantly recognizable from the beloved children's show "Jen Shriver the Science Diver."
A humane, autonomous drone equipped with a modified Arc Thrower. Capable of projecting arcs of lightning through multiple targets. Does not need to recharge between shots.
The SEAF standard assault rifle, balancing power, fire rate, and weight for a reliable weapon against smaller targets.
Gifted to Helldivers whose civilian lives were distinguished by exemplary citizenship, patriotism, and service to the Federation.
A vastly improved afterburner is installed giving the EAGLE a faster pull out time and shortening the time before it is ready to attack again.
A thermite grenade designed to adhere to surfaces before burning at 2000°C. Capable of burning through some armor.
A backpack-mounted Hellbomb that can be armed by the wearer or an ally, starting a countdown. Users are recommended to remove the backpack before the countdown reaches zero.
Equipped with the latest computational systems, subsystems, and supersystems, this armor is worth the equivalent of a small Megacity.
Adds a weapon function that increases or decreases damage, but which also increases or decreases heat build-up.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The orbital stun is a special shot fired from the Helldiver Destroyers 408mm cannons containing multiple devices that with sound, light, and electromagnetic pulses disorient and disables a wide variety of targets temporarily. While the Helldivers are trained to withstand this effect it can still severely lower your combat efficiency should you be hit, though that is preferable to death.
The Orbital Gatling Cannon has been equipped with a splurge friendly drum, increasing the fire time from 4.5 to 9 seconds
A barrage of bombs creating a non-targeted carpet of explosions.

The base module for all Helldivers.
Gives the Helldiver a few basic tools before choosing other ship modules.
Increases the fire rate of the weapon.
Prevents <c=#COLOR>all damage from bleeding</c> if chest hemorrhages.
A manned gun emplacement offering superior firepower against lightly armored targets. Slow to turn, so place it wisely.
Fires a ballistic dart at near-supersonic speeds, allowing the user to stim allies from a distance. Might sting.
The standard heatsink for laser rifles.

(NOT YET IMPLEMENTED) The 'DEFENDER' uses a proprietary 12.5mm-long pistol-style cartridge that packs one hell of a punch.

The on-top magazine holds 30 rounds, and a special recoil system coupled with the low rate of fire makes this an extremely stable gun for full-auto fire.
Incendiary capsules that contain E-710 and a primer, sets targets on fire.
A medium armored transport vehicle accomodating a crew of 4. A driver, a gunner for the 40mm autocannon, and 2 seats in the transport compartment armed with STALWART LMGs.
Featuring patented reverse-seam technology, to reduce the likelihood of bodily fluids entering the armor's interior.
Fires a spray of steel spikes that spread over distance.

A single fin-stabilized round packed to the brim with high-explosive compound. Essentially like firing small hand grenades but with very little shrapnel. Good against light and medium armored enemies.
Fires a spray of lead balls that spread over distance.
The standard shotgun ammunition type. Great for close combat and extremely effective against lightly armored targets. Virtually useless against armor.
Wearer makes <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c> less noise when moving.
Improved high speed servos allow for the turret to rotate significantly faster.
Made famous by the SEAF commander of the same name, this seal reminds us that only perfect Unity can ensure perfect Freedom.
A linear artillery barrage which moves at intervals, driving the enemy out from cover while allowing an advance.
All Hail the Helldivers, whose resplendent honor makes Tyrants tremble.
The omission of upper-limb coverings allows for optimized freedom of movement, perspiration, and communication of upper body strength to squadmates.
All Hail the Helldivers, who bring untold abundance to Super Earth's citizens.
A subdued cape, for those who need no recognition—save that of their enemies, as their executioner.

Often showcased in the "Obedient Democracy Support Troopers" cartoon, this assault rifle comes with a convenient ammo counter and compass.
Produced by Martian Armory.
The bombs are filled with more napalm at higher pressures, resulting in larger areas covered in fire.
This grenade delivery drone follows the user until it detects an enemy nearby, then flies toward it and explodes on impact. Has a limited battery life.
Based on a SEAF Signaller's Cape, which was intended to enable easy location of fallen heroes by aerial recovery crews.
The explosive compound is switched out for a more powerful one, resulting in more damage.
Armor piercing bullet with improved penetration capabilities.
A symbol of fierce commitment to Liberty and Democracy, this cape celebrates the Helldivers who have held true to Super Earth values through rain or shine.
Single high velocity sabot that does massive damage and has high armor piercing capability.
A Hellpod containing four supply packs, to replenish personal ammunition and stims in the field.
A melee weapon tipped with electrified prongs that temporarily stun targets. Can be wielded one-handed.
A sight with thin features to maximize visibility of the target.
The featherlight construction belies the heavy burden this cape entails—to live the Creed of the True Citizen.
Armor Piercing Tipped Ammunition that does less damage to unarmored targets.
The heavy rubber tunic and reflective limb guards, originally designed to save citizens from burning buildings, now enable the liberal application of the cleansing fires of Justice.
A modified Breaker shotgun firing birdshot, small pellets which saturate an area to clear up smaller targets.
A shovel that can be used as a melee weapon or, more conventionally, to dig holes in the ground.
The number of times the Energy shield emplacement can be called in is increased from 3 to 4 times.
Modeled after the myriad Statues of Judicious Liberty, who keep a watchful eye on checkout lines, schoolyards, perpetual rehabilitation communities, and public confession theaters.
The Light Machinegun is equipped with a larger magazine, with its capacity increased from 75 to 150 rounds.
When wearers stand shoulder to shoulder, this cape shows them as they truly are: an unbreakable defense, keeping Freedom safe behind an impregnable wall.
The turret is equipped with a drum magazine, significantly improving ammunition capacity.
The Rail Cannon target lock-on time is decreased by 1 second.
Allows the swift completion of Liberty's administrative tasks in an invigorating atmosphere.
Granted to the Truth Enforcers' Informant of the Month, this tasteful cape conjures images of dissident blood on asphalt.
A throwable device engineered to bounce when hitting the ground, releasing bursts of electricity on each impact. Warning: may bounce unpredictably.
Plasma cored warhead that detonates with super heated gas.
Heavily insulated from animal bites, enemy fire, and the histrionic diatribes of anarchists.
The backpack is loaded with 5 more magazines.
A shotgun used in colonies to hunt and protect from threats.
The thumper is equipped with a piston, used for sending out strong vibrations into the ground, which disrupt nearby bug nests.
A prolonged barrage, wreaking extended destruction over a large area. Communication with teammates is advised.
The missile has a larger explosion radius.
A upgraded shotgun ammunition type. Great for close combat and extremely effective against lightly armored targets. Virtually useless against armor.
An anti-tank homing missile which must lock onto its target before launch. Effective against large and armored enemies.
Higher quality servos makes the sentry capable of rotation and elevation at the same time. Also slightly improves the speed at which it turns.
A barrage of smoke grenades, creating a thick smoke screen to block enemies' line of sight.

NOT IMPLEMENTED The 'Sickle' was developed as a response to the first insurrection on Marre IV where the Deathtrooper unit of the Helldivers quickly became starved for ammunition and had to resort to melee combat against the renegade colonists.
A silo that fits one single, powerful missile. Comes with a handheld targeting remote.
Single slug that does massive damage
A laser rifle firing a continuous beam. Does not need reloading, but if it overheats a new heat sink must be fitted.
Provides <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c> resistance to gas damage and effects.
The wheels can take more damage before they are destroyed.
The crew has prepared ammunition for your equipment ahead of time and stand ready to fill a new pod. Cooldown is reduced by 30 seconds.
Plasma cored warhead that detonates with super heated gas.

Inspired by the trailblazing agents of the Super Earth Terraforming Company. These rugged adventurers surveyed hostile new planets during the post-GW1 Great Expansion era, preparing the untamed frontier for rapid and efficient assimilation.
The standard scope for most weapons, provides a good and accurate scope picture.
With this cape we honor the bio-warfare pioneers of Division Zero, conscripted from quarantine zones and hospices to spread their Carcino-Plague on the battlefield.

NOT IMPLEMENTED Used as the Super Earth Armed Forces standard answer to armored opposition, the recoilless rifle offers great anti armor capabilities in a very portable package. The weapon system requires support ammunition carried in a separate backpack and is best operated as a two man team with the loader carrying ammunition. The weapon can be reloaded by the weapon operator in a pinch should he have ammunition available.
Improved gunpowder propels the projectile at higher velocity reducing the travel time and increasing damage.
Those who serve Liberty from the shadows often elect to stay anonymous, moving like traceless specters through the night. May they watch over us always.
A plasma rifle that fires bolts of superheated gas, which can be charged by holding down the trigger. Charging up a shot fully makes the bolt explode on impact.
Fires a rocket that detonates within proximity of a target, and deploys a cluster of explosive bomblets.
Armor piercing bullet with improved penetration capabilities.
A silenced assault rifle with a built-in suppressor, which won't alert distant targets to the user's position.
Expanding projectile that does massive damage against unarmored targets.
The gas-operated, semiautomatic P-113 chambers the 14mm "Rapid Deliberation," the largest centerfire cartridge of any magazine-fed pistol.
Contains a grain of sand from Super Earth—so its bearers carry a small piece of Liberty with them, wherever they go.
Encloses the wearer in a spherical shield which blocks high-speed projectiles.
Each round is filled with more explosive mass contributing to a slightly larger explosion.
A basic iron sight for Helldivers who want to relive the glorious struggles of their ancestors.
The magazines are loaded with a 8mm APT bullet every third round. This makes it more effective against heavy infantry units.
A triple-barreled, break-action, sawed-off shotgun. Switch firing modes to fire all three barrels at once.
Adjusted tension on the breech lock results in faster projectile speed, at the cost of increased recoil.
A half-constricted muzzle that forces the shotgun pellets together into a somewhat tighter group.
The crew has been drilled to reload the cannon faster, reducing the time between uses. Cooldown is lowered by 15 seconds.
The standard 20mm AP-E round is an armor piercing projectile with a small amount of explosive mass, designed to breach through lighter armor and then explode inside.
Modeled after the Statue of Mournful Liberty, who weeps over the existence of tyranny, this armor is worn by those who would give their lives to dry her tears.
Fires two large armor piercing darts.
Shell contains three heavy projectiles that cause massive damage to unarmored targets.
A lightweight melee weapon that temporarily stuns enemies.
The Commando is equipped with missiles that have higher Armor Penetration.
A Hellpod containing four supply packs, to replenish personal ammunition and stims in the field.
Spattered gore marks those heroes who braved the harrowing first days of the war for Managed Democracy.
Air brakes and smart acceleration protocols allow for longer time with nose on target. Extends the fire time and area coverage for each run with 30%.

Since ancient times, the yellow line has symbolized an uncrossable boundary. To don this cape is to draw that line between tyranny and liberty, between alien monstrosities and Super Earth property, and never yield the right of way.
The shield power is boosted significantly, resulting in the shield being able to take double the amount of punishment before failing.
The Walking Barrage will fire two more salvoes.
All but ensures ascension to the immortal ranks of those enshrined in the Super Earth Digital Archive of Valorous Acts.
The set's classic advertising campaign "Have you tried a grenade?" has remained unchanged for over 70 years.
0.05% of profits are donated to Superstone National Park, as part of the Ministry of Unity's "Greener Galaxy" campaign.
Though originally intended solely for ceremonial use, its inspirational energy proved equally useful on the battlefield.
A speargun firing heavy-duty projectiles. These projectiles release a cloud of gas on impact, and must be carefully loaded one at a time.
Woven in honor of our loyal Helldivers, whose commitment to Democracy, through rain or shine, is an inspiration to all.
A constricted muzzle that forces the shotgun pellets together into a tighter group.
A heatsink with thinner cooling elements, improving cooling rate.
A fully-automatic pistol with an extremely high fire rate, allowing for efficient crowd control.
Round with high armor piercing capability due to the inner core forged out of Super Uranium. Added effect is radiation damage.
A tube red dot sight with 2x magnification, good for hitting small targets consistently over medium range.
As the electric arc generates a strong magnetic field, wearers should avoid use while in vicinity of stapled paperwork.
Debuted during the New Mombasa Armor Show, this sleek ensemble is sure to turn heads and blow minds.
Let all who see this cape be struck still with Freedom's beauty, or struck dead with Liberty's bullets.
Punisher shotgun variant modifier with burst fire of incendiary round and a large drum magazine.
Launches a prolonged barrage of napalm shells over a wide area, setting a swath of land ablaze in mere moments.
A larger heatsink that can store more heat.

NOT IMPLEMENTED The 'REDEEMER' is a fully automatic pistol with an extremely high rate of fire. The pistol gets very hard to control when firing full auto and is recommended for short range use only.

The burst mass of the pistol is unparalleled by other sidearms and pointing it at a target and unloading the entire magazine will put down most light to medium targets.
The Machinegun sentry's magazine capacity is increased from 125 to 200 rounds.
This armor is based on the antique uniforms of the 'Super Earth Legion', a less patriotic precursor to the Helldivers.
This cape reminds us that even faced with the abyssal darkness of space, nothing can stand against our human ingenuity, our powers of collaboration, or our sheer overwhelming numbers.
A camo paint job for use in arctic environments.
Some say that a mere glimpse of this cape, fluttering majestically in the breeze, is enough to spur a squad to victory.
A turret firing powerful shells in a high arc. Effective at long ranges, and able to strike at targets behind cover.
Expanded bomb racks allows for more bombs in each run, cutting a bigger swath out of the enemies' numbers.
The Gatling mount magazine can carry more rounds.

A variation of the Buckshot round but with small steel spikes instead of lead balls. Does less damage but handles armor better and maintains more destructive capabilities over longer range. The spread can be modified by a choke (muzzle attachment) to be tighter or spread differently over longer distances.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The best minds of Super Earth have over the years realized that rotary weapon systems shoot, a lot. They have since conceived of an orbital version of the rotary weapons commonly mounted on Helldiver vehicles and Hellpod stratagems.
A prism which creates a more focused beam that has better armor piercing at the best angle and worse armor piercing in all other angles.
Emblazoned with the red, white, and green of the 676th Democracy Regiment, who made their final stand on the slopes of Justice Hill.
Expanding projectile that does massive damage against unarmored targets.
A thinner bomb casing allows for more explosives in each bomb. Increases explosion radius.
An improved mix of flash fragments, senor disrupting drugs and chaff material extends the duration of the Static Field Conductors by 5 seconds.

A one-handed device that deploys a wide energy barrier in front of the user. The barrier is semipermeable and blocks high-speed projectiles from the outside only, leaving the user free to shoot through it.
Due to the enhanced strength caused by this armor, caution is advised when using door handles or embracing colleagues.
A grenade that releases a cloud of toxic gas, effective at temporarily blinding and slowing both organic and inorganic enemies.
A version of the standard drum but with better ergonomics.
A grenade launcher effective against armored infantry. Not intended for use against vehicle armor or fortified buildings.
This armor set first appeared in the music video for the summer anthem 'Our Love is Like Liberty (Indestructible)'.
The missile is deployed faster from the silo, reducing the deploy time from 3 to 0.5 seconds.
A single precision shot from the Destroyer's 'ATLAS' cannon.
Ammo capacity in each turret increases from 400 to 600 rounds.
Reduces range at which enemies can detect the wearer by <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c>.

[NOT IMPLEMENTED] The 'BREAKER' is a fully automatic low-recoil 12g shotgun. Its close-combat capabilities are terrifying and it can use a wide range of specialized ammunition, making it a very effective weapon on mid-range and crowd suppression.

Produced by Browfors Arms, the shotgun is used in the SEAF as a room clearing weapon and in rare cases as fire support.
Temporarily stuns all targets within the effective radius.
Contains many small pockets, allowing the user to evenly distribute the weight of ammunition, samples, and cool rocks.
Woven in honor of our loyal citizens, who by raising their voices have supported the war effort more than they can ever know.
A compact version of the Liberator designed for increased viability in close quarters. Has an increased fire rate at the cost of higher spread.
Aspect-seeking air-to-air missiles, to eliminate most flying targets in the vicinity.
The standard magazine for 15mm JAR rounds.
Expanded bomb racks allows for more bombs to be dropped each run, resulting in a longer line of napalm.
A heavily-armored walking exosuit equipped with dual autocannons.
Reduces the size of the muzzle flash by dispersing the burning propellant when firing the weapon.
Legend tells of the unnamed Helldiver, wandering the edges of Super Earth's reach, delivering Democracy and leveling lawlessness wherever the tumbleweeds lead. Wear this, and keep the legend alive.
A drill capable of piercing the tough walls of Terminid hives, and deploying a nuclear charge to collapse all tunnels.
A plasma rifle, firing a bolt of superheated gas which explodes on impact. Avoid standing in proximity to the blast.
Multiple low damage pellets for unarmored targets.
Redirects propellant gases to compensate for muzzle climb when firing the weapon.

NOT IMPLEMENTED The Expendable Anti-Tank is a one shot support weapon specialized at taking out armored targets. Though you can carry only one, they are cheap and easy to deploy and can serve as a great on demand anti-armor weapon should you encounter unexpected enemy armor.
A high-velocity railcannon round fired at the largest target in close proximity to the beacon. Targeting is automatic.
The heavy machine gun now has a smaller recoil with sustained fire. Sadly, we could not improve the recoil for the first few shots.
A barrage of rocket pods, which the Eagle pilot will release on the largest target near the stratagem beacon.
A improved targeting system allows the Static Field Conductors to be deployed at the target area 2 seconds faster.
Round with high armor piercing capability due to the inner core forged out of Super Uranium. Added effect is radiation damage.
A recoilless rifle effective against vehicle armor. Includes support backpack required for reloading.
Improved guidance programming and propulsion boosters makes them hit with even more consistency.
Increases reload speed of primary weapons by <c=#COLOR>#BONUS</c>.
Round that on impact explodes into shrapnel.
This ceremonial rifle is modeled after antique relics from pre-Democratic times. It is traditionally gifted to every citizen upon turning 16 to encourage service.
A strafing run of the battlefield to clear small targets, delivered almost instantly.
On impact the projectile melts the armor of the target.
When children have trouble sleeping, tucking them in under this cape reminds them that they are never alone, for Liberty's unseen defenders are always watching over them.
The Hellpod is loaded with two machineguns so you can spread the joy or maybe have a spare when you do not have time to reload.
After colonists of Hellmire recovered a lost shipment of this armor, the local pastime of fence-smashing was born.
The Walking Barrage will fire 2 more bombs per salvo.
The turret interprets Helldivers' commands, and no longer requires line of sight to marked targets.
Deploys a defensive anti-personnel minefield, to halt enemy advance.
A plasma igniter that reduces the spread of the plasma bolt.
Increases initial inventory and holding capacity of stims by <c=#COLOR>#SIGN#BONUS</c>.
An experimental weapon which prioritizes armor penetration. Must be charged between shots - so choose targets carefully.
The Combat Walker's fuel capacity is increased by 50%.
Gives better general recoil and less noise at the cost of ergonomics.
A powerful plasma weapon that fires one blast at a time, each blast exploding on impact. Must be charged to fire. Warning: do not overcharge.
One of the earliest to be mass-produced, this cape has been the final sight of untold numbers of Freedom's foes.
The number of times the Anti-Personnel Mine Deployer emplacement can be called in is increased from 3 to 4 times.
Body type has no impact on gameplay
This bolt-action rifle fires jet-assisted shells that explode shrapnel in all directions upon impact. Not recommended for close-quarters use.
Each purchase of this cape comes with a complimentary will and testament amendment form, which guarantees the soon-to-be-deceased a prominent spot on the Wall of Martyrs.
Every other projectile have been replaced with a armor piercing round to make it more efficient against armored infantry units.
A one-handed ceremonial sword suitable for use in parades, sabrage, and combat.
The number of times the Defense wall can be called in is increased from 5 to 6 times.
Heavy Projectile with better damage and ballistics, the downside is the worse accuracy.
The AAPF rounds are designed for surface to air combat against lightly armored fliers.

Heavily layered to protect against ocular blistering, subdermal liquification, and gastrointestinal shattering, this armor is a testament to the power of iterative improvements based on user feedback.
The installation of an auto-loader allows the crew to fill a reloadable magazine, reducing the time between uses. Cooldown is lowered by 30 seconds.
Scatters powerful anti-tank mines that deal heavy, armor-penetrating damage. Minefield is less densely packed relative to smaller mines.
A magazine that contains more rounds at the cost of number of magazines. It allows the Helldiver to carry more overall ammo and reload less often.
Armor Piercing Tipped Ammunition that does less damage to unarmored targets.
